# J.Crew Video Generator

A Next.js 16 app that scrapes J.Crew product pages, generates fashion walk-through videos via Kling AI (fal.ai), and renders a storefront preview with hover-to-video.

## Tech Stack
- Next.js 16 (App Router, Turbopack), Tailwind CSS v4, TypeScript
- cheerio for server-side HTML scraping
- @fal-ai/client for Kling video generation via fal.ai
- Browser localStorage for persistence (no database)

## Project Structure
```
src/
├── app/
│   ├── page.tsx                    # Main workflow: URL → Select Images → Generate → Review
│   ├── preview/page.tsx            # J.Crew-style storefront with hover-to-video cards
│   ├── test-scrape/page.tsx        # Diagnostic: scrape a category, show image selection for 20 products
│   ├── api/scrape/route.ts         # POST: scrape a single J.Crew product page
│   ├── api/scrape-category/route.ts# POST: scrape product URLs from a category page
│   ├── api/generate-video/route.ts # POST: submit to fal.ai Kling API
│   └── api/video-status/route.ts   # POST: poll fal.ai for video completion
├── components/
│   └── ProductCard.tsx             # E-commerce card with hover crossfade to video
└── lib/
    ├── types.ts                    # Shared types: ScrapedProduct, ScrapedImage, Product, VideoJob
    ├── scraper.ts                  # J.Crew scraping: gallery extraction, image classification
    ├── fal.ts                      # fal.ai client: Kling O3 video submission + polling
    └── storage.ts                  # localStorage CRUD for approved products
```

## Workflow
1. User pastes a J.Crew product URL
2. Server scrapes the page, extracts gallery images from `[class*="product-gallery-container"]`
3. User selects which images to use (first 3 pre-selected)
4. First selected image = `start_image_url`, all selected = elements
5. Submits to fal.ai Kling O3, polls for completion
6. User reviews video, approves → saved to localStorage → shown in storefront preview

## Environment
- `FAL_KEY` in `.env.local` — fal.ai API key (server-side only)
